replies.body:
@FeralPony
Sorry FeralPony but this position did not convinced me. (Fail to) Control of Riven's passive due to the difficulty of tracking it is exactly the reason why I gave up adding Riven to my champion pool when I was trying to find an AD Caster for me to master. It is really annoying to keep alternating eye saccades* between the buff bars and the down and dirty of a crowded fight that often requires tunnel-vision for her playstyle.

* http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saccade

But for your description of this test I believe you did the bar the wrong way. It should work as Renekton or Rengar resource bar, which indeed increases at the uses of skills or (in Renekton's case) attacks, and when full is the moment Riven should be the most dangerous. The bar on a high-CDR Rengar is a rollercoaster; I cannot but frown at your point about "dumping their entire bar in one go" as a relevant concern, because this should work similar to Rage and Ferocity, not Mana or Energy.
{{champion:58}}  & {{champion:107}} 
I do wish for your team to review this; I know that your Diamond 1 testers deem this clarity cost too high but we, not so high Elo players that wish to learn an already-very high skill cap champion, would be throwing money at our screens to pay for this QoF that just separates us of mastering Riven and being better players.
{{champion:92}}
